-- Russian Rescuers Save 23 From Novgorod Psychiatric Hospital Fire
-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2013-09-13T05:26:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-13/russian-rescuers-save-23-from-novgorod-psychiatric-hospital-fire.html
Russian rescue squads saved 23
people from a fire that broke out in a mental hospital in the
Luka village in the Novgorod Region today, according to the
website of the local unit of the Emergencies Ministry.  The fire started at 2:52 a.m. local time, according to the
statement. There were 59 patients and an undisclosed number of
personnel in the hospital at the time, according to RIA Novosti.  Oleg Voronov, a spokesman for the Emergency Ministry’s
Novgorod branch, wasn’t available immediately to comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
